cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.SE 

The paper discusses machine learning on Big Data using the MapReduce programming paradigm, which is commonly used in distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the limitations of MapReduce and proposes an extension called Iterative MapReduce, which involves optimization techniques. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper involves data analysis and inference, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases).
